<subSubSection id="0DB15E8CFFD7E564FF0CD5F0FA9C55A4" pageId="6" pageNumber="239" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="45140D07FFD7E564FF0CD5F0FAF554DB" blockId="6.[151,1436,151,501]" pageId="6" pageNumber="239">
<emphasis id="77DFD115FFD7E564FF0CD5F0FEF1549C" bold="true" box="[199,321,151,176]" pageId="6" pageNumber="239">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Male dichoptic; dorsocentrals 1+3; katepisternals equidistant one from each other; fore tibia with setulose hairs, denser and longer in male; male mid tibia reddish towards middle; hind femur reddish-orange on basal two-thirds to four-fifths; hind tibia broad, concave on ventral margin and with one anteroventral seta.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="45140D07FFD7E564FF0CD463FA9C55A4" blockId="6.[151,1436,151,501]" pageId="6" pageNumber="239">
<emphasis id="77DFD115FFD7E564FF0CD463FECC5531" box="[199,380,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="239">Male terminalia</emphasis>
. Very peculiar. Sternite 5 broad at base, with posterior membrane deep and lobes straight and very elongated; with few setae on disc and short hairs at tips of lobes, which are yellow (
<figureCitation id="DD901182FFD7E564FB49D440FB65556C" box="[1154,1237,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–19" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1968,1991]" captionTargetBox="[201,1417,209,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[176,1417,193,1949]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 17–19. Helina hirtiPes metatarsalis Emden, 1951, paratype male: (17) sternite 5, dorsal view; (18) cercal plate and surstylus, dorsal view; (19) cercal plate, surstylus and aedeagal complex, lateral view. Scale bar 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1207166/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="239">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
); cercal plate and surstylus very elongated (
<figureCitation id="DD901182FFD7E564FE7ED42BFDB85548" box="[437,520,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–19" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1968,1991]" captionTargetBox="[201,1417,209,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[176,1417,193,1949]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 17–19. Helina hirtiPes metatarsalis Emden, 1951, paratype male: (17) sternite 5, dorsal view; (18) cercal plate and surstylus, dorsal view; (19) cercal plate, surstylus and aedeagal complex, lateral view. Scale bar 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1207166/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="239">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
); surstylus longer than cercal plate and with an elongated process on inner margin in apical fourth (
<figureCitation id="DD901182FFD7E564FE9AD408FE1455A4" box="[337,420,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–19" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1968,1991]" captionTargetBox="[201,1417,209,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[176,1417,193,1949]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 17–19. Helina hirtiPes metatarsalis Emden, 1951, paratype male: (17) sternite 5, dorsal view; (18) cercal plate and surstylus, dorsal view; (19) cercal plate, surstylus and aedeagal complex, lateral view. Scale bar 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1207166/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="239">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
); aedeagal complex with distiphallus short, postgonite with short setae (
<figureCitation id="DD901182FFD7E564FB07D408FAAF55A4" box="[1228,1311,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–19" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1968,1991]" captionTargetBox="[201,1417,209,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[176,1417,193,1949]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 17–19. Helina hirtiPes metatarsalis Emden, 1951, paratype male: (17) sternite 5, dorsal view; (18) cercal plate and surstylus, dorsal view; (19) cercal plate, surstylus and aedeagal complex, lateral view. Scale bar 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1207166/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="239">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0DB15E8CFFD7E564FF0CD4F3FD1F55D9" pageId="6" pageNumber="239" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="45140D07FFD7E564FF0CD4F3FD1F55D9" blockId="6.[151,1436,151,501]" pageId="6" pageNumber="239">
<emphasis id="77DFD115FFD7E564FF0CD4F3FEA15581" bold="true" box="[199,273,404,429]" pageId="6" pageNumber="239">Notes.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="77DFD115FFD7E564FED3D4F2FE215581" box="[280,401,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="239">H. hirtipes</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="213A70F6FFD7E564FE6BD4F3FDE45581" box="[416,596,404,429]" pageId="6" pageNumber="239" refId="ref4566" refString="Macquart, P. - J. - M. (1846) Dipteres Exotiques nouveaux ou peu connus. Supplement. Memoires de la Societe des Sciences, de l'Agriculture et des Arts a Lille, 1844, 133 - 364." type="journal article">Macquart, 1846</bibRefCitation>
) is the 
<typeStatus id="9A10B3A5FFD7E564FD63D4F2FD685581" box="[680,728,405,429]" pageId="6" pageNumber="239">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName id="82AB7684FFD7E564FC9CD4F3FBC35580" authority="Malloch, 1921" authorityName="Malloch (Malloch" authorityYear="1921" box="[855,1139,404,429]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Idiopygus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="77DFD115FFD7E564FC9CD4F3FC755581" box="[855,965,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="239">Idiopygus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="213A70F6FFD7E564FC06D4F3FBC35580" box="[973,1139,404,429]" pageId="6" pageNumber="239" refId="ref4609" refString="Malloch, J. R. (1921) Exotic Muscaridae (Diptera). - III. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, 8 (9), 225 - 239. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222932108632584" type="journal article">Malloch, 1921</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, now a junior synonym of 
<emphasis id="77DFD115FFD7E564FF5CD4D0FF5355FC" box="[151,227,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="239">Helina</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="77DFD115FFD7E564FF3FD4DEFDB255FC" box="[244,514,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="239">H. hirtipes metatarsalis</emphasis>
was described as a subspecies. 
<emphasis id="77DFD115FFD7E564FCBFD4DEFBFC55FC" box="[884,1100,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="239">H. hirtipes hirtipes</emphasis>
could not be dissected as no material was available in the 
<collectionCode id="23BA95C2FFD7E564FE15D4BAFD8255D8" box="[478,562,477,500]" pageId="6" pageNumber="239">BMNH</collectionCode>
collection.
</paragraph>
